properties.Name: CarcassQualityGrade

Columns.Name: CarcassQualityGradeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a carcass quality grade.

Columns.Name: CarcassQualityGradeName
Columns.Description: The name of a carcass quality grade.

Columns.Name: CarcassQualityGradeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of a carcass quality grade.

Properties.Description:
An estimate of palatability based primarily on marbling and maturity and generally to a lesser extent on color, texture and firmness of lean. Days on feed and fat thickness (of 0.25 inches or more) are comparable to quality grade in estimating eating quality.

USDA Quality Grades are an assessment of eating quality and are determined by carcass maturity and marbling. 

There beef carcass maturity: A, B, C, D and E.
